          <p>While Southwest Louisiana doesn't get extreme cold, temperatures can drop into the 30s during winter months. A malfunctioning furnace means discomfort for your family and potential risks to pipes and property. Our certified technicians diagnose furnace problems accurately and provide honest recommendations—we'll repair your system when possible and only recommend replacement when it's truly necessary.</p>

          <h2>Common Furnace Problems We Repair</h2>
          <p>Our technicians are experienced with all types of furnace issues, from simple fixes to complex repairs:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Furnace Not Heating:</strong> The most common complaint—we identify whether it's a thermostat issue, pilot light problem, ignition failure, or more serious component failure.</li>
            <li><strong>Furnace Blowing Cold Air:</strong> Often caused by thermostat settings, clogged filters, or pilot/ignition issues. We diagnose and fix the root cause.</li>
            <li><strong>Strange Noises:</strong> Grinding, squealing, banging, or rumbling sounds indicate specific problems that we can identify and repair.</li>
            <li><strong>Frequent Cycling:</strong> If your furnace turns on and off too frequently, it could be a thermostat, airflow, or flame sensor issue.</li>
            <li><strong>Pilot Light Problems:</strong> Pilot lights that won't stay lit often indicate thermocouple issues or gas supply problems.</li>
            <li><strong>Ignitor Failure:</strong> Modern furnaces use electronic ignition—we repair and replace faulty ignitors.</li>
            <li><strong>Blower Motor Issues:</strong> Problems with the blower motor affect airflow and heating performance.</li>
            <li><strong>Gas Valve Problems:</strong> Issues with the gas valve can prevent proper fuel delivery to the burners.</li>
          </ul>

